[size=5][b]ClothesDryer — turn an Improvised Wardrobe into a powered clothes dryer[/b][/size]

A server-side mod for [b]SCUM dedicated servers[/b]. An [b]Improvised Wardrobe[/b], once activated with a build recipe, becomes a [b]clothes dryer[/b]: wet clothing (and worn bags/backpacks) left inside it dries automatically while a player is nearby. No more standing around a fire in your underwear.

Everything is driven from [b]normal in-game chat[/b] (type [b]dryer[/b] for the command list). No client mod — players need nothing installed, so [b]client BattlEye stays on[/b].

[size=4][b]⚠ Server operators only[/b][/size]
This runs inside your dedicated-server process via UE4SS. Installing it requires file-system access to the server. It does nothing on a game client and cannot affect a server you don't control. Use it on your own / authorised servers only.

[size=4][b]How it works[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Build and place an [b]Improvised Wardrobe[/b] in your flag.
[*]Put the recipe inside — [b]5× Metal Scraps + any Alternator + 1× Wire + 5× Bolts[/b] — and type [b]dryer activate[/b]. The recipe is consumed and the wardrobe becomes a dryer (remembered by location, so it survives renames and restarts).
[*]Drop wet clothes (or worn bags/backpacks — they're clothing too) inside. They dry within a few seconds while you're nearby. Water containers like canteens are never touched.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]A SCUM [b]dedicated server[/b] you administer (SteamCMD app 3792580).
[*][b]UE4SS injected server-side[/b] (the setup other SCUM server mods use), able to load into SCUMServer.exe.
[*]In [b]ue4ss\UE4SS-settings.ini[/b]: [b]HookProcessInternal = 1[/b] and [b]HookProcessLocalScriptFunction = 1[/b] (needed for the chat trigger).
[/list]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Copy the [b]ClothesDryer[/b] folder AND the [b]shared[/b] folder into your server's UE4SS mods directory:
[code]<server>\SCUM\Binaries\Win64\ue4ss\Mods\ClothesDryer\
<server>\SCUM\Binaries\Win64\ue4ss\Mods\shared\Scripts\gating.lua[/code]
[*]Open [b]ClothesDryer\Scripts\main.lua[/b] and set [b]MOD_DIR[/b] to that folder's full path.
[*][i](Optional — only for the per-player donation model.)[/i] Drying works out of the box with no database. Granting access to specific players ([b]dryer add <player>[/b]) reads SCUM.db via [b]sqlite3.exe[/b] and is [b]off by default[/b]. To enable: download the [b]sqlite3.exe[/b] CLI tool from [url=https://sqlite.org/download.html]sqlite.org[/url], keep ONE copy on the server (e.g. in [b]Mods\shared[/b]), and set [b]sqliteExe[/b] in Config to that path (or [b]"sqlite3.exe"[/b] for PATH). Default-on and per-flag overrides never need it.
[*]Enable it in [b]...\ue4ss\Mods\mods.txt[/b]:
[code]ClothesDryer : 1[/code]
Do [b]not[/b] create [b]enabled.txt[/b] — it silently overrides mods.txt.
[*]Start the server and type [b]dryer[/b] in chat for the full command list.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Notes[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Drying needs a player nearby — SCUM keeps container contents live only while observed, so an abandoned closed wardrobe pauses until someone's around (which is whenever anyone actually uses it).
[*]Still looks wet right after it dries? The server already set it dry; your client re-syncs a beat later or on reopening the wardrobe.
[*]Pairs with my [b]WashingMachine[/b] mod — wash the dirt out there, dry it here.
[*]The [b]shared[/b] folder is a small library shared by my SCUM mods — if you already have it from another of my mods, the copy is identical.
[*]All rights reserved. Personal use on servers you administer; please don't re-upload or repackage.
[/list]
